\par }}{\f2  }{\b\f2 How to make your own Flash cards
\par }\pard \widctlpar {\b\f2 
\par }\pard \widctlpar {\f2 
To make your own Flash cards first open the study file you wish to use (either an existing one or a new one you name yourself) then select File from the menu, then select Edit Cards. If this is a new file you are creating then one blank card will be autom
atically created for you ready to edit. Simply add the text you want on the card and press one of the buttons (New, Apply, or Ok) to save it.
\par }\pard \widctlpar {\f2 
\par }\pard \widctlpar {\f2 If you intend to make many cards then the N
ew button is your best option: After you edit the card and press New it first saves that card and then creates a new one automatically ready to edit. To speed up the process you can use the Tab key to move from the Question box to the Answer box after you
 fill in your question, then from the Answer box to the New button after you fill in your answer. When you are all done do NOT press the New button again as this will make yet another card. Press OK instead to save your work and quit the Edit Cards dialog
 (the same button to use if you make just one card).
\par }\pard \widctlpar {\f2 
